Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
moveGroupPins(25.10)                                      moveGroupPins(25.10)

Name
       moveGroupPins  -  Changes  the pin layer, the pin size, pin status, re-
       solves pin overlap, and moves a selected pin or pin group to a specific
       location

Syntax
       moveGroupPins

       [-help]

       [-depth <float>]

       [-end_location {<x y>}]

       [-expand_spacing_factor <float>]

       [-layer <string>]

       -loc {<x y>}

       [-moveOnLayer <string>]

       [-noFixed]

       [-spacing <float>]

       [-spread_type <string>]

       [-start_location {<x y>}]

       [-width <float>]

       [-withOverlap]

       Changes the pin layer, the pin size, pin status, resolves pin  overlap,
       and  moves  a selected pin or pin group to a specific location. You can
       use this command after selecting the pin(s) in the move mode (selecting
       pins in the design display area with the Move/Resize/Reshape tool  wid-
       get).

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each moveGroupPins parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man moveGroupPins

       -depth <float>
              Specifies the depth of the pin or pin group, in micrometers.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -end_location {<x y>}
              Specifies the coordinates where the pins  should  end  when  the
              pins are spread along a range.

              Data_type: point, optional

       -expand_spacing_factor <float>
              Specifies the value that will be multiplied to the current spac-
              ing in tracks.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -layer <string>
              Specifies  the  number  of  the  metal  layer for the pin or pin
              group.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -loc {<x y>}
              Specifies the new x and y location for the pin or pin group.

              Data_type: point, required

       -moveOnLayer <string>
              Specifies that the pin(s) can be moved UP or DOWN  to  the  next
              preferred layer.

              Note:  If  an attempt is made to move the pin(s) beyond the min-
              max layer range or to an illegal layer (such as over the  parti-
              tion-reserved  or design-restricted layer), the tool displays an
              error, and no pin movement occurs.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -noFixed
              Specifies that the moved pins or group of pins are  not  set  to
              the fixed status.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -spacing <float>
              Specifies the spacing between pins for multi-pin editing.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -spread_type <string>
              Specifies  how  spacing  between  pins  is  managed while moving
              grouped-pins.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -start_location {<x y>}
              Specifies the coordinates where the pins should start  when  the
              pins are spread along a range.

              Data_type: point, optional

       -width <float>
              Specifies the width of the pin or pin group, in micrometers.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -withOverlap
              Specifies that moved pin(s) can overlap.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
       The  following  command  moves the selected pin group to a new location
       (10,20):

       moveGroupPins -loc 10 20

